column11: Impressive split level Victorian family home Full of light and space, this stylish split level Victorian residence enjoys rear elevation with private leafy outlooks just footsteps from Annandale\'s cafe lifestyle. column11: Premier Location - Two Lots on Large 306m2 Block **AUCTION THIS SATURDAY** This is a rare opportunity for developers or investors to capitalise on a prime piece of Annandale real estate. This double front home was once two workers cottages on separate titles with deep set-rear gardens and loads of possibilities to renovate, restore and recreate! Create a large family home, rebuild the dividing wall and resume its two dwelling configuration, or extend and redevelop as per similar surrounding homes (subject to council approval). Never has there been so much choice! Ideal for those looking for something a little different with comfortable interiors and a convenient location close to Annandale village shops. Two good sized bedrooms each with built-in wardrobes, high decorative ceilings, picture rails and one with ceiling fan Open plan dining area with spiral staircase to an expansive separate living room on the lower level Gourmet-style gas kitchen with central island bench, granite bench tops and European s/steel appliances Undercover balcony off kitchen / dining area offers additional outdoor entertaining space Sun-drenched rear yard with paved area, easy-care landscaped garden and single carport  Huge bathroom and laundry on lower level with separate bath and shower Cellar room and storage, polished timber floors throughout Easy walk to popular Annandale shops and eateries, parks and schools Land Area: 126.5m2 Water Rates: $173 per quarter Council Rates $275 per quarter Figures approximate only.

Revamped Victorian semi with studio Lifestyle - A wonderful purchase for those who love the convenience of village living, this beautifully refurbished 1886 semi takes pride of place on a picturesque tree-lined street just footsteps to local shops and cafes. Designer interiors and classic features give it immense appeal. Accommodation - Three bedrooms, the third contained within a large separate rear guest studio, elegant lounge room with gas fire, gracious skylit dining room with gas fire, smart CaesarStone gas kitchen with original Aga stove, two charming heritage bathrooms, main with a clawfoot bath.  Features - Covered side deck with in-built bbq, deep timber-decked courtyard, stylish black Japan floorboards, high ornate ceilings, a/c, built-ins, plantation shutters, security system, ornate cornices, pretty facade, ceiling fans, skylights, rear lane access to LUG with storage.

Elegant Urban Oasis Lifestyle - Period charm, spacious interiors and exceptional entertaining areas are the hallmarks of this freestanding single level character home of rare elegance and uncompromising quality. Quietly set on a generous and supremely private block of land in one of Annandale\'s premier streets, "Omega" circa 1884 enjoys a central yet tranquil position just a stroll to village cafes and restaurants, parks and city buses and is very convenient to light rail, the CBD, Blackwattle Bay, harbour foreshores walks and Leichhardt\'s popular dining precinct. Accommodation -Tastefully restored and immaculately presented, "Omega" combines the graceful features of yesteryear with a contemporary sensibility. Behind a deceptively restrained faAade lies an expansive home of generous proportions and a host of retained period features. It offers separate formal living and dining rooms, two double bedrooms, an oversized fully-equipped gas kitchen with ample storage, large bathroom featuring quality brass fixtures and a concealed internal laundry.  Features - A stunning Anthony Wyer designed garden provides a lush and very private focal point for outdoor entertaining. Featuring a fish pond, elevated and paved alfresco dining area, established plants and full irrigation, it creates a stylish urban oasis. Indoors, additional features including extra-high ornate ceilings, period detailing throughout, two magnificent gas fireplaces in the living areas plus another two ornate fireplaces in the bedrooms, tessellated entrance tiles, stained glass feature windows and entrance door, plantation shutters and air conditioning. There is handy rear lane pedestrian access and a garden storage shed with extra w/c.

Refurbished Victorian home near Rozelle Bay Freestanding and newly refurbished, this Victorian home boasts a prized address in Annandale\'s north and is ready to enjoy now. It presents immaculately and offers an easycare lifestyle near parklands surrounding Rozelle Bay and within minutes of the city. Air conditioned open plan living/dining, modern gas kitchen Great flow-through to a sunny courtyard for alfresco dining Two double sized bedrooms, one with built-in wardrobes Quality stainless steel Bosch appliances include dishwasher Full bathroom has a wall of glass bricks for natural light A fully equipped laundry area concealed in the bathroom High ceilings and timber floors throughout, attic storage Fenced forecourt area, secure side access to the kitchen Ample on street parking, a few minutes\' walk to light rail Near fine schools, village shopping, cafes and city buses
